<br>
1. You pulled the warlord and one or more additional mobs.  You rooted the warlord, but the root broke.<br>
<br>
2. The mob aggroed Samadeb's group.  They did not cause the root to break.  They did not pull the mob to their camp.  They did not interfere with your attempt to control the mob.  In short, they did not KS you by any definition of that term.  Instead, they got attacked by a mob that you had pulled, and they defended themselves.<br>
<br>
3. The warlord dropped a T staff, which was randomed and won by Samadeb.<br>
<br>
We don't see any wrongdoing here by anyone.  Samadeb and his groupmates could have chosen to give the T staff to you, but they had no moral obligation to do so.  The mob attacked them, they killed it, they got the loot.<br>
<br>
We will accept for argument's sake your assertion that you had been camping the warlord for several days.  You have not claimed that Samadeb or his group invaded your camp or KSed a mob that you were camping.  You simply lost control of the mob and essentially trained it on Samadeb's group, apparently while they were fighting other mobs.<br>
<br>
We understand your disappointment, but you have simply not been wronged here. <p>Sagemon Prayeth<BR>
